# React Conventions

## Components

- Functional components only -- no class components
- Named exports for all components and hooks
- Props destructured in the function signature

```jsx
// Good
export function PokemonCard({ id, name, sprite, onClick }) {
  return (
    <button onClick={() => onClick(id)}>
      <img src={sprite} alt={name} />
      <span>{name}</span>
    </button>
  );
}

// Bad: default export, class component, props not destructured
export default class PokemonCard extends React.Component { ... }
```

## File Organization

- Reusable components in `src/components/`
- Route-level screens in `src/pages/`
- Custom hooks in `src/hooks/`
- Pure utility functions in `src/utils/`

## Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes exclusively
- No inline `style` attributes
- Mobile-first responsive design with Tailwind breakpoints

## Hooks

- Custom hooks prefixed with `use` (e.g., `useLocalStorage`, `usePokemon`)
- Keep hooks in `src/hooks/` for reuse across components
- Avoid side effects directly in component bodies -- use `useEffect`
